# Firebase Admin SDK (server-only, for import API).
# Option A (recommended): absolute path to service account JSON (required on Windows).
#   Place service-account.json in project root or a secure folder, then in .env.local:
#   GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=C:\Users\YourName\Downloads\sf\service-account.json
#   PowerShell: use forward slashes or escaped backslashes; absolute path avoids "16 UNAUTHENTICATED".
# Option B: individual env vars (private key: literal \n in .env, code replaces with newline).
# FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=stockforgeai-fa6b8
# FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=firebase-adminsdk-xxx@stockforgeai-fa6b8.iam.gserviceaccount.com
# FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
# Firebase Storage bucket for Admin SDK (server-only; required for CSV upload). Use bucket ID, e.g. project.appspot.com or project.firebasestorage.app
# FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=stockforgeai-fa6b8.firebasestorage.app
# After changing any of the above, restart the dev server (npm run dev).
